#. <section class="sutta" id="sn10.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.11:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga"
msgstr "1. With Indaka"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn10.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Cīrāsutta"
msgstr "11. With the Nun Cīrā"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.11:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn10.11:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

#. VAR: cīrāya → cirāya (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn10.11:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako cīrāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ adāsi."
msgstr "Now at that time a certain lay follower gave a robe to the nun Cīrā."

msgctxt "sn10.11:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho cīrāya bhikkhuniyā abhippasanno yakkho rājagahe rathikāya rathikaṃ "
"siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then a native spirit was so devoted to Cīrā that he went street to street "
"and square to square, and on that occasion recited these verses:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.460"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc845"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.11:2.1"
msgid "“Puññaṃ vata pasavi bahuṃ,"
msgstr "“O! He has made so much merit!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.11:2.2"
msgid "Sappañño vatāyaṃ upāsako;"
msgstr "That lay-follower is so very wise."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.11:2.3"
msgid "Yo cīrāya adāsi cīvaraṃ,"
msgstr "He gave a robe to Cīrā,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: vippamuttiyā”ti → vippamuttāyāti (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn10.11:2.4"
msgid "Sabbayogehi vippamuttiyā”ti."
msgstr "who is released from all bonds.”"
